Kevin W. Crull  President of Omnichannel Sales, Sprint CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 2 Board Members in 2 different organizations across 9 different industries.See Board Relationships52$3,572,477As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Kevin W. Crull has been President of Omnichannel Sales at Sprint Corporation since November 2016. Mr. Crull has been the Chief Executive Officer of CTV Inc. since April 2011. Mr. Crull served as the President of The Central and Northeast Areas at Sprint Corporation from May 2015 to November 26, 2016 and served as its President of the Central Area since December 11, 2015 and Chief Marketing Officer from May 31, 2015 to December 12, 2015. Mr. Crull was responsible ... for all products and services, brand and advertising, customer acquisition and retention and all digital and social efforts. He served as the President of Bell Media Inc. (formerly, CTV globemedia) of BCE, Inc. from April 1, 2011 to April 9, 2015. He has more than 30 years of experience leading sales, marketing and operational teams, with more than a decade in each of telecommunications and consumer packaged goods. He served as the Chief Operating Officer of Bell Media from November 2010 to April 1, 2011. He served as the President of Residential Services of Bell Canada, Inc. since September 2, 2005 until January 1, 2011, where he launched FiberTV and was responsible for wireline, high-speed Internet and video services. Previously, Mr. Crull served as President of Consumer Solutions of Bell Canada from February 2005 to September 2005 and was responsible for sales, marketing, customer care and product development for its wireline, wireless, Internet and digital television services. He served as Chief Operating Officer of CTVglobemedia at Bell Canada, Inc. since January 2011. He joined Bell Canada in early 2005. He served as Senior Vice President and General Manager of Wireless Business/Services at&T Corp. since March 25, 2004. He served as Senior Vice President of AT&T Consumer and Small Business Division of AT&T Corp. from 2001 to 2004. He served as Senior Vice President of Marketing and Sales of Consumer Division at&T. Mr. Crull joined AT&T in June 2001. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of ESP Networks Inc., a wireless venture. He spent five years at US West as Senior Vice President of the Consumer Services Group. He served nine years with Nestlé SA, where he advanced from an entry level position to Division Vice President of Beverage Sales. He has been a Director of SickKids Foundation since June 2011. Mr. Crull serves as a Member of Advisory Board of Kensington Capital Partners Limited. He served as a Director of Bell Aliant Regional Communications Holdings Inc. of Bell Aliant Inc. since July 2006. He served as a Director of Bell Aliant Regional Communications Inc., General Partner of Bell Aliant Regional Communications, Limited Partnership from July 2006 to June 14, 2011. Mr. Crull served as a Director of Bell Aliant Inc. (a/k/a Bell Aliant Regional Communications Income Fund) until June 2011. He serves on the board of the Center for Telecommunications Management at the University of Southern California. He is a Strong Supporter of the national fundraising event, Walk for Kids Help Phone. He holds a Bachelor's degree in Marketing from Ohio State University and an MBA from the University of San Francisco. He has also completed leadership development programs at the Dale Carnegie and Aspen Institutes.Read Full Background




